<frame name="FR_Speak_on_topic" ID="10054" xsi:schemaLocation="../schema/frame.xsd" xmlns="http://framenet.icsi.berkeley.edu" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" domains="Verbal_communication">
    <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;A &lt;fen&gt;Speaker&lt;/fen&gt; speaks about a particular &lt;fen&gt;Topic&lt;/fen&gt;, to an &lt;fen&gt;Addressee&lt;/fen&gt;.  
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
Verbs in this frame do not allow local realization of the full &lt;fen&gt;Message&lt;/fen&gt; itself (in particular a message in the form of a sentential complements is not possible). Nouns in this frame either refer to nominalizations referring to the act of talking about a topic, or refer to the &lt;fen&gt;Message&lt;/fen&gt;.
&lt;ex&gt;FR-EX: La &lt;t&gt; déposition&lt;/t&gt;  de &lt;fex name="Speaker"&gt;Pierre&lt;/fex&gt; sur &lt;fex name="Topic"&gt;l'agression&lt;/fex&gt; a duré 3 heures.&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;ex&gt;FR-EX: &lt;fex name="Message"&gt;La &lt;t&gt;déposition&lt;/t&gt;  de Pierre&lt;/fex&gt; contient des erreurs.&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
This frame differs from other communication frames in that the full &lt;fen&gt;Message&lt;/fen&gt; itself cannot be realized locally (except it is reffered to by some nouns of this frame).
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;asf&gt;Distinctions with other frames&lt;/asf&gt;:
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;

≠ &lt;frframe&gt;FR_Statement-manner-noise&lt;/frframe&gt;: for FR_Speak_on_topic's LUs, the complement is not understood as the actual words (except if other signs such as quotes indicate it) but as a Topic, discussed possibly at length. The &lt;fen&gt;Message&lt;/fen&gt; cannot be realized locally (except for nominalizations). 

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;asf&gt;Relation to fndata-1.5&lt;/asf&gt; : This frame is a generalization of the Speak_on_topic frame. The &lt;fen&gt;Message&lt;/fen&gt; FE is added, to cope with nominalizations that refer to the message pronounced by the &lt;fen&gt;Speaker&lt;/fen&gt; The  &lt;fen&gt;Audience&lt;/fen&gt; FE is renamed &lt;fen&gt;Addressee&lt;/fen&gt; and is not necessarily passive.
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    <FE bgColor="008000" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="605" cDate="01/23/2003 07:42:02 PST Thu" abbrev="" name="Addressee" ID="4134">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The person or persons to whom the &lt;fen&gt;Speaker&lt;/fen&gt; delivers their message.

&lt;ex&gt;He &lt;t&gt;lectured&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Audience"&gt;to the officers of the Scots Guard&lt;/fex&gt;  in  1929.&lt;/ex&gt;&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="FF0000" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="605" cDate="01/23/2003 07:42:17 PST Thu" abbrev="" name="Speaker" ID="4135">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The person who orally delivers a message about a &lt;fen&gt;Topic&lt;/fen&gt; to an &lt;fen&gt;Addressee&lt;/fen&gt;.

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Speaker"&gt;You&lt;/fex&gt; have to &lt;t&gt;sermonize&lt;/t&gt; about the good times&lt;/ex&gt;&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
        <semType name="Sentient" ID="5"/>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="0000FF" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="605" cDate="01/23/2003 07:47:29 PST Thu" abbrev="" name="Topic" ID="4136">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;What the message that the &lt;fen&gt;Speaker&lt;/fen&gt; produces is about.

&lt;ex&gt;He was the Director: he could &lt;t&gt;lecture&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Topic"&gt;on whomever he liked&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="808080" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="296" cDate="07/17/2001 03:05:17 PDT Tue" abbrev="" name="Medium" ID="4878">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The written material that contains the message.
&lt;ex&gt;FR-EX: &lt;fex name="Medium"&gt;Le document&lt;/fex&gt; évoque des malversations.&lt;/ex&gt; &lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="8080FF" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="296" cDate="07/17/2001 03:05:17 PDT Tue" abbrev="" name="Message" ID="4879">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The message expressed by the &lt;fen&gt;Speaker&lt;/fen&gt; 
This FE is used for nominalizations refering to the message, or in case of parenthetical clauses.
&lt;ex&gt; FR-ex: &lt;fex name="Speaker"&gt;Le premier ministre&lt;/fex&gt; a critiqué l'attentisme, dans &lt;fex name="Message"&gt;une &lt;t&gt;allusion&lt;/t&gt; transparente au parti travailliste&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;ex&gt; FR-ex: &lt;fex name="Message"&gt;Les fermiers sont responsables de ce qu'il s'est passé&lt;/fex&gt;, a &lt;t&gt;commenté&lt;/t&gt;  &lt;fex name="Speaker"&gt;le commissaire central&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
